[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     5[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;208;135;112m>[38;2;208;135;112m The code maps to the seven core pseudocode steps from the main recipe: activate the session and capture audio (Step 1), stream audio to ASR and finalize the transcript (Step 2), parse the command into intent and slots (Step 3), resolve context and disambiguate (Step 4), confirm write-class commands and execute read-class commands directly (Step 5), execute against the EHR and reflect the result (Step 6), and audit and emit telemetry (Step 7). The synthetic clinicians, patients, schedules, medications, and command transcripts in the demo are fictional; the names, MRNs, and other identifiers are obviously made-up and should not match anyone real.[K
