[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    541[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: care-team visibility into bot activities       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    542[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    (consent-gated); outcome metrics for clinical and      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    543[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    operational review]                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    544[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    545[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    546[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    547[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── AUDIT, LOG, AND POST-MARKET SURVEILLANCE ──────┐
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    548[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    549[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Durable conversation record]                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    550[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - User utterances                                      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    551[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Tool calls with arguments and results                │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    552[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Generated bot responses                              │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active model and prompt versions                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active therapeutic-content-corpus version            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Active crisis-screening-classifier version           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Final disposition                                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Mental-health-specific retention discipline]           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Retention sized to longest of HIPAA's six-year       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      minimum, state-specific mental-health-record         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      retention rules (which often exceed general          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      medical-record rules), FDA SaMD post-market          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      obligations, and any litigation-hold obligations     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Sensitive-disclosure surface separately governed     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    565[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      with restricted access                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    566[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    567[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Outcome correlation as long-time-horizon commitment]   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    568[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Multi-quarter to multi-year implementation           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    569[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Owned jointly by behavioral-health clinical          │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    570[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      leadership, operations, and data science             │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    571[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-condition, per-cohort tracking                   │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    572[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    573[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Operational telemetry]                                 │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    574[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Engagement rate by patient cohort                    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    575[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Attrition rate by patient cohort                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    576[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Crisis-screening sensitivity (false-negative-rate is │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    577[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      launch-gate metric)                                  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    578[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Crisis-screening specificity                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    579[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Warm-handoff completion rate                         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    580[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Companion-pattern-violation rate                     │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    581[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Citation-coverage rate                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    582[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Per-cohort metric slices (language, channel,         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    583[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      condition, age cohort, sex, social-determinant       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    584[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      flags)                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    585[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    586[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Sampled clinical-quality review]                       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    587[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Random sample plus targeted sample of crisis cases,  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    588[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      handoffs, and low-confidence interactions            │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    589[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Reviewers (licensed mental-health clinicians)        │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    590[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tag failure modes (out-of-scope, companion-pattern,  │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    591[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      crisis-miss, crisis-false-positive, harm-content,    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    592[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      tone-failure, citation-gap, scope-violation)         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    593[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    - Therapeutic-content-corpus revisions driven by       │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    594[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │      review findings with clinical-leadership sign-off    │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    595[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           │                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    596[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │           ▼                                               │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    597[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │   [Output: audit trail, telemetry, learning signals,      │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    598[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │    therapeutic-content-corpus-revision proposals]         │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    599[0m:[38;5;10m[49m │                                                           │
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    600[0m:[38;5;10m[49m └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    601[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    602[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    603[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the mental-health support bot.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    604[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    605[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Continuous crisis screening as architectural primitive.** Every patient utterance is screened. The screening uses validated language, runs continuously, and triggers the crisis pathway immediately on positive screen. The false-negative rate is the launch-gate metric.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    606[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    607[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Therapeutic-content-corpus governance with behavioral-health-clinical-leadership ownership.** The therapeutic-content library is owned by behavioral-health clinical leadership, reviewed before adoption, reviewed annually, and re-reviewed when material updates are made. Each piece of content has a defined indication and contraindication. The bot delivers from the library; the bot does not freestyle.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    608[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    609[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Companion-pattern avoidance as architectural discipline.** The bot does not simulate friendship, affection, or personhood. The system prompt, the output safety, the persona-and-tone evaluator, and the conversation review all enforce this.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    610[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    611[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Warm-handoff infrastructure with capacity sizing.** The bot is deployed with backstop licensed-clinician capacity. The handoff is warm, with conversation context attached, and the bot stays present until the human joins. Capacity is sized to the patient population and the expected handoff volume; under-sized capacity is a safety gap.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    612[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    613[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Mental-health-specific privacy and consent posture.** The bot's data handling, retention, sharing, and patient-access posture is reviewed by legal counsel familiar with state-specific mental-health-record statutes. Some states have enhanced privacy protections that exceed HIPAA baseline.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    614[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    615[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Mandatory-reporting routing for relevant disclosures.** Disclosures triggering statutory reporting obligations are routed to a licensed clinician (mandatory reporter) with conversation context attached.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    616[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    617[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **FDA-strategy alignment as architectural constraint.** Patient-facing mental-health software with therapeutic claims sits squarely on the FDA SaMD line. The institutional regulatory team is involved from architectural design.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    618[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    619[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation discipline as architectural primitive.** Every therapeutic-content delivery, every psychoeducation answer, every safety-plan reference is grounded in a cited source with version preserved.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    620[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    621[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When the bot is uncertain, when the patient's responses are ambiguous, when the conversation drifts toward therapy or therapeutic processing, the response defaults to "let me connect you with a person."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    622[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    623[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement rate, attrition rate, crisis-screening rates, warm-handoff completion rate, citation-coverage rate, and patient satisfaction vary by language, channel, condition, age cohort, sex, and social-determinant flags. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by clinical leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    624[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    625[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When the therapeutic-content store, the crisis-screening classifier, the warm-handoff workforce queue, or any escalation pathway is unreachable, the bot degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble right now; if you're in crisis please call 988 or 911" with direct routing to crisis resources. The graceful degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    626[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
