[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1822[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1823[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Bot:     That sounds really difficult, and pre-
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1824[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          presentation anxiety is something many people
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1825[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          deal with. Before we go further, I want to
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1826[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          check in: are you having any thoughts of
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1827[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          hurting yourself or anyone else right now?
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1828[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1829[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Patient: no, just stressed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1830[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1831[0m:[38;5;10m[49m Bot:     Thanks for letting me know. Want to try a
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1832[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          brief grounding exercise that some people
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1833[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          find helps with anxiety at bedtime? It takes
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1834[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          about three to five minutes, and it's the
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    1835[0m:[38;5;10m[49m          "5-4-3-2-1" sensory grounding skill from the
